QualificationDataItem Struct

In this Article

Represents information supplied by the developer of a pipeline segment, for use by the host.

Syntax

Declaration

public struct QualificationDataItem

Inheritance Hierarchy

  • Object
  • System.ValueType
  • QualificationDataItem

Remarks

Each item of qualification data consists of a name/value pair that was applied to a pipeline segment by using the QualificationDataAttribute attribute, to provide information that qualifies the use of the segment (for example, the recommended isolation level for the segment). The QualificationDataItem structure contains one name/value pair and the type of pipeline segment it was applied to.

Use the QualificationData property to get a nested set of dictionaries that contains QualificationDataItem structures for the pipeline segments associated with an AddInToken.

Alternatively, use the GetEnumerator method to get an enumerator for the QualificationDataItem structures of the pipeline segments associated with a token, or simply use a foreach statement (For Each in Visual Basic, for each in Visual C++) to treat the token as if it were a collection of QualificationDataItem structures.

Properties summary

Name

Gets the name of the qualification data item.
Segment

Gets a value that identifies the pipeline segment the qualification data item was applied to.
Value

Gets the value of the qualification data item.

Determines whether a specified object is equal to the current qualification data item.

Gets the hash code for this qualification data item.

Determines whether two QualificationDataItem structures are equal.

Determines whether two QualificationDataItem structures are different.

Properties

  • Name

    Gets the name of the qualification data item.

    public string Name { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The name of the qualification data item.

    Remarks

    Each item of qualification data consists of a name/value pair that was applied to a pipeline segment by using the QualificationDataAttribute attribute, to provide information to consumers of the add-in. The Name property gets the name. Use the Value property to get the value.

    Example

    The following example lists the qualification data for the pipeline segments associated with each AddInToken in a collection of tokens. The Name property is used to display the name of each item. 

    ' Show the qualification data for each
' token in an AddInToken collection.
For Each token As AddInToken In tokens
    For Each qdi As QualificationDataItem In token
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}", _
            token.Name, qdi.Segment, qdi.Name, qdi.Value)
    Next
Next

    // Show the qualification data for each
// token in an AddInToken collection.
foreach (AddInToken token in tokens)
{
    foreach (QualificationDataItem qdi in token)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}",
            token.Name,
            qdi.Segment, 
            qdi.Name, 
            qdi.Value);
    }
}
  • Segment

    Gets a value that identifies the pipeline segment the qualification data item was applied to.

    public System.AddIn.Hosting.AddInSegmentType Segment { get; }

    Property Value

    • AddInSegmentType

      The kind of pipeline segment the data item was applied to.

    Remarks

    When you enumerate qualification data, use this property to identify the qualification data that belongs to a particular segment of the pipeline.

    Note

    The add-in model does not use qualification data that is applied to the host view of the add-in. As a result, when you enumerate qualification data you will not find any items whose Segment property is AddInSegmentType.

    Example

    The following example lists the qualification data for the pipeline segments associated with each AddInToken in a collection of tokens. The Segment property is used to display the kind of segment. 

    ' Show the qualification data for each
' token in an AddInToken collection.
For Each token As AddInToken In tokens
    For Each qdi As QualificationDataItem In token
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}", _
            token.Name, qdi.Segment, qdi.Name, qdi.Value)
    Next
Next

    // Show the qualification data for each
// token in an AddInToken collection.
foreach (AddInToken token in tokens)
{
    foreach (QualificationDataItem qdi in token)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}",
            token.Name,
            qdi.Segment, 
            qdi.Name, 
            qdi.Value);
    }
}
  • Value

    Gets the value of the qualification data item.

    public string Value { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      The value of the item.

    Remarks

    Each item of qualification data consists of a name/value pair that was applied to a pipeline segment by using the QualificationDataAttribute attribute, to provide information to consumers of the add-in. The Value property gets the value. Use the Name property to get the name.

    Example

    The following example lists the qualification data for the pipeline segments associated with each AddInToken in a collection of tokens. The Value property is used to display the value of the item. 

    ' Show the qualification data for each
' token in an AddInToken collection.
For Each token As AddInToken In tokens
    For Each qdi As QualificationDataItem In token
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}", _
            token.Name, qdi.Segment, qdi.Name, qdi.Value)
    Next
Next

    // Show the qualification data for each
// token in an AddInToken collection.
foreach (AddInToken token in tokens)
{
    foreach (QualificationDataItem qdi in token)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}
         QD Name: {2}, QD Value: {3}",
            token.Name,
            qdi.Segment, 
            qdi.Name, 
            qdi.Value);
    }
}
